text: Alice DeeJay was a Dutch electronic music group, who achieved success from 1999 to 2002. The group consisted of record producers Pronti (born Sebastiaan Molijn), Kalmani (born Eelke Kalberg) and DJ Jurgen, with lead singer Judith Anna Pronk. The groups best known song is "Better Off Alone" from their 2000 album, Who Needs Guitars Anyway?. ==Other websites== *Alice DeeJay at Allmusic Category:1990s Dutch music groups Category:2000s Dutch music groups Category:Electronic music groups Category:Musical groups established in 1999 Category:1999 establishments in Europe Category:1990s establishments in the Netherlands Category:Musical groups disestablished in 2002 Category:2002 disestablishments in Europe Category:Entertainers from Amsterdam
